frameDefinitions: This frame concerns people being in an altered mental state that is induced by an Intoxicant.
A Traveller boards a Vehicle that they intend to use as a means of transportation either as a passenger or as a driver.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
A Traveller leaves from or dismounts a Vehicle.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
frameExamples: On the 5th of December, 1834, we <t>embarked</t> on board the merchant ship Hellespont.

The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
